cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of unsupervised domain adaptation in image classification, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces regularization techniques and evaluates the proposed framework on a neuromorphic vision sensing (NVS) sign language recognition dataset, which could potentially fall under the categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
